http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/EPFO-withdraws-grace-period-of-5-days-for-remittances/article13999173.ece

The Employeesâ€™ Provident Fund Organisation has directed the employers to pay the contributions and administrative charges within 15 days of close of every month as per the provisions of EPF and MP Act, 1952 without availing any grace time.A grace period of five days has been provided till now to considering additional time needed for remittance in the banks. Assistant PF Commissioner Dasarathi Nag said in a press note that due to technological advances, the additional time had been withdrawn as everyone opts for electronic challan-cum-return (ECR) facility.This will be applicable from next month.The release stated that the new system will come into force from February for depositing contributions for the month of January that is payable in the month of February.The employers will therefore need to deposit the remittances within 15 days of close of every month from February.